WEBVTT

00:11.178 --> 00:13.220
♪♪

00:57.011 --> 00:59.220
-[water trickling]
-[birds tweeting]

01:09.428 --> 01:11.929
[quacking]

01:16.970 --> 01:19.136
I like this, you know?

01:19.136 --> 01:21.720
I like the ducks.
Make Way for Ducklings.

01:21.720 --> 01:23.762
You ever read that to your kids?
You got kids, right?

01:23.762 --> 01:25.845
[laughs] Anyway, the ducks,
they make me laugh.

01:25.845 --> 01:27.762
They always look
so fucking busy.

01:27.762 --> 01:29.428
[Jackie]
Why are you so nervous, Jimmy?

01:29.428 --> 01:31.595
[Jimmy] Huh? What the fuck
do I got to be nervous about?

01:31.595 --> 01:33.637
[Jackie] You're starting
to sound like an asshole.

01:33.637 --> 01:35.470
[Jimmy]
Yeah? Yeah?

01:35.470 --> 01:37.512
Well, I'm on a comedown,
you know?

01:37.512 --> 01:39.553
A bit of a high. I'm just
getting a little antsy.

01:39.553 --> 01:41.637
-The bodies, Jimmy.
-Yeah, like I said.

01:42.804 --> 01:44.887
I might have heard
something.

01:46.804 --> 01:48.887
I think I might know
where the armored car is.

01:48.887 --> 01:50.595
Your story's
already changing.

01:50.595 --> 01:52.387
You got to be
more trusting, pal.

01:52.387 --> 01:53.804
Why'd they disappear
the truck

01:53.804 --> 01:55.679
if there are no
fucking bodies in it, huh?

01:55.679 --> 01:57.387
Come on.

01:57.387 --> 01:59.095
I mean, I know you think
I'm dumb.

01:59.095 --> 02:00.970
Everybody thinks I'm dumb.
I talk too much.

02:00.970 --> 02:02.470
But I'm fucking
smart enough to know

02:02.470 --> 02:03.845
that this is a big deal
for you,

02:03.845 --> 02:05.303
this Revere thing.

02:05.303 --> 02:07.053
Armored car,
a couple dead guards.

02:07.053 --> 02:08.887
You could ride a case like this
to your fucking pension.

02:08.887 --> 02:10.637
Oh, there it is.

02:10.637 --> 02:12.637
That's what all this
duck shit has been about.

02:12.637 --> 02:14.845
Jimmy Ryan is setting me up
for a fucking favor.

02:14.845 --> 02:16.637
No favors.

02:16.637 --> 02:17.929
No immunity. No protection.

02:17.929 --> 02:19.804
Money, 20,000.

02:19.804 --> 02:21.637
Immunity from what?

02:21.637 --> 02:23.303
I got two little girls
in Florida,

02:23.303 --> 02:25.512
and they never had their
fucking father read them

02:25.512 --> 02:27.387
Make Way for Fucking Ducklings,
okay?

02:27.387 --> 02:30.011
-I need fucking money.
-Well, you know,

02:30.011 --> 02:31.762
I mean, there's only so far
that Uncle could go

02:31.762 --> 02:33.804
with this type of thing.

02:33.804 --> 02:36.679
Are you gonna cry "poor man"
with me? Huh? Huh?

02:36.679 --> 02:38.345
You're the great
Jackie Rohr.

02:38.345 --> 02:40.428
Jimmy, Jimmy, God,
give me something tangible

02:40.428 --> 02:42.011
that I can hand up
to Uncle.

02:42.011 --> 02:44.512
Let Uncle know that
you're being a good boy.

02:44.512 --> 02:46.470
-Come on.
-Okay.

02:46.470 --> 02:48.762
Well, this Revere thing...

02:51.512 --> 02:53.512
it's about how bad
you want it, Jackie.

02:55.303 --> 02:56.845
How far are you
willing to go?

02:56.845 --> 02:58.387
Let me ask you something, Jimmy.

02:58.387 --> 03:00.387
Do you remember how hard those
black parents fought

03:00.387 --> 03:02.095
to get their kids
on those buses?

03:02.095 --> 03:03.720
All the shit that they went
through to make sure

03:03.720 --> 03:06.387
that their kids went to those
lily-white schools.

03:06.387 --> 03:09.345
And then the Mau Mau
source out Charlestown High

03:09.345 --> 03:10.720
where their kids
were being bussed,

03:10.720 --> 03:12.470
and they figured out

03:12.470 --> 03:14.762
that they were just as big
shitholes

03:14.762 --> 03:16.929
as the ones in Roxbury.

03:16.929 --> 03:18.637
And they realized

03:18.637 --> 03:20.637
what white people
have known all along:

03:20.637 --> 03:22.929
that they were just fighting for
peanuts in somebody else's shit.

03:22.929 --> 03:24.387
So how far am I willing to go?

03:24.387 --> 03:26.387
Well, the counterpoint
to that is, is it worth it?

03:26.387 --> 03:29.470
And the concluding thought
there is that you

03:29.470 --> 03:34.303
better be fucking careful
what you wish for.

03:34.303 --> 03:36.220
And just so we're clear here,
all right?

03:36.220 --> 03:38.929
Just so you understand
my meaning,

03:38.929 --> 03:40.845
what I'm saying is,

03:40.845 --> 03:44.387
if I fucking go to bat for you
with this shit,

03:44.387 --> 03:47.011
you better hope
to fucking Christ

03:47.011 --> 03:49.845
that I'm not left
picking peanuts

03:49.845 --> 03:52.387
out of someone else's shit.

03:54.428 --> 03:55.387
Okay.

03:59.345 --> 04:00.929
You'll give me 20 grand?

04:00.929 --> 04:03.762
How far are you willing to go,
Jimmy?

04:07.387 --> 04:08.887
The Ebb Tide.

04:11.011 --> 04:12.595
What the fuck
do I do with that?

04:12.595 --> 04:14.428
That's where
they got their guns.

04:29.553 --> 04:31.053
Hey! Hey, Jackie!

04:31.053 --> 04:32.970
Jackie!

04:32.970 --> 04:34.637
What about the 20 grand?

04:36.053 --> 04:38.470
You gotta be
more trusting, pal.

04:39.637 --> 04:41.053
[ducks quacking]

05:09.053 --> 05:10.970
Hey, how was New Hampshire?

05:14.512 --> 05:16.887
The fuck you grinning about?

05:16.887 --> 05:19.178
Guys, this is too much.

05:19.178 --> 05:20.762
You might be
the only person on earth

05:20.762 --> 05:22.470
-to ever say that was a problem.
-[laughs]

05:22.470 --> 05:24.220
Well, I can't launder
this all through here.

05:24.220 --> 05:26.220
This is, like, $250,000.

05:26.220 --> 05:28.178
Yeah, and then 10%
goes to the office.

05:28.178 --> 05:29.845
Yeah, and then I can
maybe match that.

05:29.845 --> 05:31.136
How about more?

05:32.345 --> 05:34.345
We can go to the clubs.
Gamble some.

05:34.345 --> 05:36.637
And you can probably
get away with exchanging

05:36.637 --> 05:38.512
about 10 grand through there
without getting noticed.

05:40.220 --> 05:43.011
So we're supposed to just
sit on the rest?

05:43.011 --> 05:45.178
You guys dump the guns?

05:45.178 --> 05:47.387
We sold them
back to Hook.

05:49.095 --> 05:50.804
What the fuck?

05:50.804 --> 05:52.595
Why?

05:52.595 --> 05:54.553
How is anyone going
to connect us to those guns

05:54.553 --> 05:56.929
they found in the hand
of some smoke in Roxbury?

05:56.929 --> 05:58.220
Huh?

05:58.220 --> 06:00.053
Those guns turn up,

06:00.053 --> 06:02.387
there's not going to be anyone
coming to find us, Kathleen.

06:11.595 --> 06:13.929
["Real Big Leaguer"
by John Neal plays on jukebox]

06:13.929 --> 06:17.637
♪ I'm a real big leaguer ♪

06:17.637 --> 06:20.136
[chatter]

06:20.136 --> 06:22.553
♪ I'm a rock and roll singer ♪

06:26.136 --> 06:28.929
♪ I'm a real friendly guy ♪

06:30.136 --> 06:31.929
Give me a Miller Draft.

06:31.929 --> 06:34.095
Tap's dry.

06:34.095 --> 06:36.095
Give me a bottle then.

06:36.095 --> 06:38.261
Sorry, I'm just out.

06:43.136 --> 06:44.762
You're Hook, right?

06:46.095 --> 06:47.804
Do you know who I am?

06:47.804 --> 06:49.303
-I don't need to know.
-No?

06:49.303 --> 06:50.762
Because I know
what  you are.

06:52.720 --> 06:53.762
[sniffles]

06:58.970 --> 07:00.428
You know this place
you got here...

07:01.929 --> 07:04.178
it's fucking filthy.

07:05.929 --> 07:07.553
You need to get somebody
to come in here

07:07.553 --> 07:09.136
and clean this shit up.

07:09.136 --> 07:11.178
[snorts]

07:11.178 --> 07:14.136
Or you might get a visit
from the Board of Health.

07:15.887 --> 07:17.220
Oops.

07:19.303 --> 07:22.136
♪ It wasn't me,
I'm just a stranger ♪

07:25.804 --> 07:27.095
[knocks]

07:27.095 --> 07:28.804
[Hank]
Yeah?

07:33.470 --> 07:35.261
So I called the Staties
in New Hampshire

07:35.261 --> 07:37.553
about that other armored car
case, the one in Nashua.

07:38.804 --> 07:40.887
The feds already
claimed jurisdiction.

07:40.887 --> 07:43.845
So they're not saying if there's
a connection with Revere?

07:43.845 --> 07:45.220
Can I help you?

07:46.428 --> 07:48.261
Oh, um...

07:48.261 --> 07:50.804
I should be asking you.

07:50.804 --> 07:53.220
I've been assigned to you
as an investigator.

07:53.220 --> 07:55.178
Rachel Benham.

07:55.178 --> 07:57.095
Why do you look
so concerned?

07:57.095 --> 07:59.011
You ever work murder before?

08:00.011 --> 08:01.845
Oh, I see.

08:01.845 --> 08:03.970
You think you got stuck
with some fucking broad, huh?

08:03.970 --> 08:05.970
-I didn't say that.
-Okay, well,

08:05.970 --> 08:08.178
don't get confused then because
I am the one who's stuck.

08:08.178 --> 08:10.011
You're the dope who lost
the case against a kid

08:10.011 --> 08:11.970
who shot a cop.

08:13.637 --> 08:15.053
I recruited her.

08:15.053 --> 08:17.011
[Decourcy]
And you say nothing?

08:17.011 --> 08:18.970
Oh, she can take care
of herself.

08:18.970 --> 08:21.512
Yeah, clearly.
What heist in Nashua?

08:21.512 --> 08:23.011
The stuff that--

08:23.011 --> 08:25.845
Hey. Any of these
fucking cold cases

08:25.845 --> 08:27.679
connect to a bar
up in Revere?

08:27.679 --> 08:29.679
[Decourcy] Did you hear about
another armored car robbery

08:29.679 --> 08:31.804
-up in New Hampshire?
-Yeah, but the crime is federal,

08:31.804 --> 08:33.095
outside your jurisdiction.

08:33.095 --> 08:34.553
Means you can't use it.

08:34.553 --> 08:37.637
Oh, good. You got one
of every color now.

08:37.637 --> 08:39.762
-What the fuck?
-Anyway, like I was saying,

08:39.762 --> 08:41.929
any of them connect to a bar
up in Revere?

08:41.929 --> 08:43.220
It's called the Ebb Tide.

08:43.220 --> 08:46.011
Guy missing since '88.

08:46.011 --> 08:47.178
[Jackie]
Who?

08:49.679 --> 08:50.887
Kelly Kinicki.

08:58.178 --> 09:00.053
[gargles]

09:02.970 --> 09:04.345
Burn?

09:04.345 --> 09:05.804
[spits]

09:07.136 --> 09:08.595
What's up, Hank?

09:08.595 --> 09:11.261
What can you tell us
about Kinicki, 1988?

09:11.261 --> 09:13.845
Kinicki? Four years ago?

09:13.845 --> 09:16.887
You know what? I don't think
I want to talk about that case

09:16.887 --> 09:18.679
in front of a prosecutor.

09:18.679 --> 09:20.345
Prosecutor lost me
that case.

09:20.345 --> 09:21.845
Really?

09:21.845 --> 09:23.720
Because Woods said
you  blew it.

09:23.720 --> 09:25.762
Yeah? He's fucking lying.

09:25.762 --> 09:29.512
Yeah, sure, because Boston cops
never lie, right?

09:29.512 --> 09:31.887
Vern, would I
waste your time?

09:31.887 --> 09:34.553
Just tell us
what went wrong.

09:34.553 --> 09:36.178
All right, the case
was a heartbreaker.

09:36.178 --> 09:38.595
I thought I had the suspect
all lined up, and then--

09:38.595 --> 09:41.095
And then you didn't?

09:41.095 --> 09:42.595
It was a circumstantial case.

09:42.595 --> 09:44.345
But it was fucking tight.

09:44.345 --> 09:46.929
Just didn't give the DA
a lot of room.

09:46.929 --> 09:49.762
I mean, you know the odds,
you take a drug case to trial.

09:49.762 --> 09:52.303
Defendant's got a one-in-three
shot of getting off.

09:52.303 --> 09:54.095
Fucking prick wouldn't plead.

09:54.095 --> 09:55.178
[scoffs]

09:55.178 --> 09:56.804
Yet you pushed for trial?

09:56.804 --> 10:00.512
Hon, are you new at this?

10:00.512 --> 10:03.679
[rock music playing over radio]

10:03.679 --> 10:08.595
♪ Too long
I've been fallin' down ♪

10:08.595 --> 10:13.428
♪ Too long
I've been crawlin' 'round ♪

10:13.428 --> 10:16.178
♪ Too long ♪

10:16.178 --> 10:18.762
♪ Now it's time ♪

10:18.762 --> 10:22.804
♪ To rise ♪

10:24.637 --> 10:28.970
♪ So say goodbye
to the Holy Ghost ♪

10:30.595 --> 10:34.720
♪ It's too much sorrow livin' ♪

10:35.845 --> 10:37.804
♪ Come on, baby ♪

10:39.595 --> 10:42.428
♪ Easy on me ♪

10:47.095 --> 10:51.804
♪ All I got left is just
a little bit of pride, girl ♪

10:56.512 --> 10:58.345
-[door closes]
-The fuck you want?

10:58.345 --> 11:00.720
-Your husband home?
-He's busy.

11:00.720 --> 11:01.929
Yeah?

11:03.303 --> 11:05.095
Good.

11:05.095 --> 11:07.428
Because I come to confess,
I'm madly in love with you.

11:09.261 --> 11:10.595
That shit don't work
on me, kid.

11:10.595 --> 11:12.136
That shit don't work what?

11:12.136 --> 11:13.679
You're not getting any,
you understand?

11:13.679 --> 11:15.512
Is that the way
for a mother of three to talk?

11:15.512 --> 11:18.011
Not getting any what, huh?
Not getting any what?

11:18.011 --> 11:19.345
I'll slap your face.

11:19.345 --> 11:21.220
You always act like
I come by needing something.

11:21.220 --> 11:22.595
You don't give me
any fucking credit.

11:22.595 --> 11:24.595
Yeah, well,
I never see you otherwise.

11:24.595 --> 11:26.053
-[Jimmy] Yeah, yeah, yeah.
-Mom?

11:26.053 --> 11:28.136
-Yeah?
-[Jimmy] Oh. Sweetie.

11:28.136 --> 11:31.053
Oh. What's the matter, hon?

11:31.053 --> 11:33.011
Your mother get jealous
of your good looks again?

11:33.011 --> 11:35.887
Would you stop it?
What do you need?

11:35.887 --> 11:37.261
Nothing.

11:37.261 --> 11:38.887
Never mind.

11:40.136 --> 11:42.345
What's the matter
with her?

11:42.345 --> 11:44.053
Nothing.
She's just tired.

11:44.053 --> 11:46.303
Yeah? Those nightmares?

11:48.178 --> 11:49.720
What does she see?

11:51.178 --> 11:53.053
-Lock your door, will you?
-Yeah.

11:53.053 --> 11:54.345
-Lock the door.
-Yeah!

11:58.845 --> 12:01.261
Frankie, I don't feel
very comfortable in this.

12:01.261 --> 12:03.595
Yeah, I know. Super sorry I made
you take off the track suit.

12:03.595 --> 12:05.553
We look like two Italian
assholes rolling in here

12:05.553 --> 12:07.261
with a wad of cash.

12:07.261 --> 12:09.470
Nobody's going to wonder
where we got it from.

12:09.470 --> 12:11.053
This should be a hoot.

12:11.053 --> 12:13.095
-Jimmy. Jimmy.
-What? What?

12:13.095 --> 12:14.512
Shut the fuck up.

12:16.387 --> 12:18.428
We're not here
to have fun.

12:18.428 --> 12:19.929
You understand?
This is work.

12:19.929 --> 12:21.261
Yeah.

12:21.261 --> 12:23.595
You don't just steal
the fucking money.

12:23.595 --> 12:25.929
You got to get away
with stealing the money.

12:27.428 --> 12:29.345
You going to throw
your accent too?

12:29.345 --> 12:31.595
Shut the fuck up.

12:31.595 --> 12:33.178
[rock music playing]

12:36.345 --> 12:37.929
[inaudible]

12:39.095 --> 12:41.929
[inaudible]

12:52.136 --> 12:54.804
[music continues,
no audible dialogue]

13:03.637 --> 13:05.261
[Jimmy]
Oh, come on, come on, come on.

13:05.261 --> 13:07.470
Oh! Man, fuck me!

13:07.470 --> 13:09.303
[rock music playing softly]

13:21.637 --> 13:23.553
[giggles]

13:25.470 --> 13:27.178
[moans]

13:37.804 --> 13:39.804
Uh, don't take this
the wrong way,

13:39.804 --> 13:42.178
but what's that thing
right there?

13:42.178 --> 13:43.679
Are you fucking kidding me?

13:43.679 --> 13:46.011
I got a wife.
You know this.

13:48.261 --> 13:49.595
[doctor]
Mr. Rhodes?

13:49.595 --> 13:50.970
Rohr.

13:52.178 --> 13:53.845
[sighs] Okay.

13:56.595 --> 13:58.595
So, what can I do
for you today?

13:58.595 --> 14:00.345
I think I need a scrape.

14:00.345 --> 14:02.261
Huh? A what?

14:02.261 --> 14:04.595
A short arm inspection.

14:04.595 --> 14:06.679
Just read
the fucking intake.

14:06.679 --> 14:07.887
Oh.

14:09.220 --> 14:10.553
Oh.

14:11.804 --> 14:13.387
Do you have any symptoms?

14:13.387 --> 14:15.428
I think I got a thing.

14:15.428 --> 14:18.637
What does your regular
physician say?

14:18.637 --> 14:21.470
Asshole, if I could go
to my regular doctor,

14:21.470 --> 14:22.553
would I be here?

14:22.553 --> 14:24.804
A confidentiality thing.

14:24.804 --> 14:26.011
Should I have
to tell you that?

14:30.303 --> 14:32.220
Okay, take it out.

14:32.220 --> 14:33.637
It's not like
I got options.

14:39.887 --> 14:41.220
[laughing]

14:42.345 --> 14:44.178
Oh, fuck.

14:44.178 --> 14:46.428
-Oh, fuck.
-Let's go.

14:46.428 --> 14:47.720
-[laughing]
-Let's go. Come on.

14:47.720 --> 14:49.595
Up, up, up.

14:49.595 --> 14:51.095
Don't you get your fucking
hands on me!

14:51.095 --> 14:52.595
-Don't you fucking touch me.
-Up.

14:52.595 --> 14:54.220
Don't you fucking--
Watch this.

14:54.220 --> 14:55.679
I go bom-bom.
That's what I go.

14:55.679 --> 14:57.637
I go bom-bom. No, I go up.

14:57.637 --> 14:59.762
-I go--
-[both grunt]

15:01.470 --> 15:03.428
Hey, come on. Get up!

15:04.595 --> 15:06.178
[laughs]

15:08.762 --> 15:11.261
-Here, you want me to drive?
-No.

15:13.553 --> 15:15.679
[sighs and pants]

15:15.679 --> 15:17.679
What are you going
to tell her?

15:17.679 --> 15:19.428
That you lost
the money?

15:19.428 --> 15:21.303
Cathy's going
to blame you anyways.

15:21.303 --> 15:22.929
[laughs]

15:27.887 --> 15:30.136
[bluesy rock music playing]

15:33.261 --> 15:35.428
[Siobhan] Are you done
staring at yourself, Decourcy?

15:44.470 --> 15:47.220
Now, would you look
at that bed in there?

15:47.220 --> 15:49.804
I bet that bed
is still warm.

15:49.804 --> 15:52.470
And I'm still so,
so cold.

15:52.470 --> 15:54.470
And then there's
that body.

15:54.470 --> 15:57.637
All that body that could
keep me warm.

15:57.637 --> 15:59.428
When the reverend
asks for testimony,

15:59.428 --> 16:03.220
you can say what strength God
gave you to resist temptation.

16:03.220 --> 16:04.637
[laughs]

16:04.637 --> 16:06.470
Guess that'll save me
from begging.

16:06.470 --> 16:08.387
[Siobhan]
You were too tired last night.

16:08.387 --> 16:10.470
Well, that's why I need
to be in the bed.

16:10.470 --> 16:12.345
-Church will take an hour.
-[tap water runs]

16:12.345 --> 16:13.679
To mourn a drug dealer?

16:13.679 --> 16:15.220
We're trying to build

16:15.220 --> 16:17.095
a political platform
in this community,

16:17.095 --> 16:19.220
and we need the reverend.

16:19.220 --> 16:21.136
Look at the weight
your daddy threw in Brooklyn.

16:21.136 --> 16:24.679
I've spent 18 years
listening to his bullshit.

16:24.679 --> 16:28.136
Pretty sure I earned the right
to skip one Sunday morning.

16:28.136 --> 16:29.178
[Siobhan]
Bullshit?

16:30.512 --> 16:33.887
Like, "My daddy knew King."

16:33.887 --> 16:36.762
"My daddy was in Memphis."

16:36.762 --> 16:40.303
♪ My daddy was in... ♪

16:40.303 --> 16:43.220
You know, that's just something
I tell the work folks.

16:43.220 --> 16:45.595
Anytime you mention
Martin Luther King

16:45.595 --> 16:47.178
or an abusive parent,

16:47.178 --> 16:48.845
they get comfortable.

16:48.845 --> 16:51.095
I'm just playing
a role they know.

16:51.095 --> 16:53.220
Then don't act righteous
with me.

16:54.553 --> 16:56.220
All right.

16:56.220 --> 16:57.553
Reverend Field
is my client,

16:57.553 --> 16:59.261
and I promised him
you'd be there.

16:59.261 --> 17:02.720
So I'm really doing you
a favor then.

17:02.720 --> 17:05.345
Mm-hmm, one that I'll
pay back.

17:05.345 --> 17:07.470
Oh, you going
to pay it back?

17:07.470 --> 17:08.720
Mm-hmm.

17:08.720 --> 17:11.178
You going
to pay it back?

17:22.095 --> 17:24.387
Our words matter.

17:24.387 --> 17:26.178
[congregants]
Yes.

17:26.178 --> 17:28.428
Our actions matter.

17:28.428 --> 17:30.387
That's right.

17:30.387 --> 17:32.178
Our culture matters.

17:34.720 --> 17:37.929
Not just to ourselves
and our sense of identity,

17:37.929 --> 17:40.845
but to the way in which
we are perceived.

17:40.845 --> 17:42.095
We are being watched.

17:43.470 --> 17:45.595
Constantly.

17:45.595 --> 17:47.595
Our errors are scrutinized.

17:48.762 --> 17:52.428
Our flaws, magnified.

17:52.428 --> 17:55.762
And though the story of this
young man before us is tragic,

17:55.762 --> 17:58.095
his death is a warning.

17:58.095 --> 18:00.261
No policeman did this.

18:02.345 --> 18:04.261
No white man did.

18:05.553 --> 18:07.178
One of our own.

18:08.637 --> 18:10.428
We are killing each other
on these streets,

18:10.428 --> 18:12.261
and the killing must end.

18:13.261 --> 18:14.887
[man] Yes.

18:14.887 --> 18:17.929
Now, the Lord's justice
is sure.

18:17.929 --> 18:20.470
And though the universe may bend
towards that justice...

18:20.470 --> 18:22.011
Who the hell is that?

18:22.011 --> 18:24.637
-We're in church.
-I don't care.

18:24.637 --> 18:27.011
I know him from work.

18:27.011 --> 18:28.136
[Reverend]
...if we want justice.

18:28.136 --> 18:30.637
And we must look to one another.

18:30.637 --> 18:33.345
You all pay taxes.

18:33.345 --> 18:36.470
You all send your babies
to these schools.

18:37.887 --> 18:39.762
This is our community.

18:39.762 --> 18:43.261
And together, we must all
bring the law home.

18:43.261 --> 18:45.178
Help me! Help me!

18:45.178 --> 18:47.804
Help me! Help me!
They'll kill me! Oh, please, no!

18:47.804 --> 18:49.762
-They'll kill me!
-[all scream]

18:49.762 --> 18:51.845
Help me! Help me!

18:51.845 --> 18:54.095
[congregants screaming]

18:54.095 --> 18:56.303
[gunshots]

19:05.887 --> 19:08.762
[all screaming]

19:27.929 --> 19:30.303
Go, go. Take her outside.

19:40.637 --> 19:42.178
[sirens wailing]

19:49.970 --> 19:51.637
[doors open]

19:53.220 --> 19:54.804
[officer] Hey, why do you got
your hands up?

19:54.804 --> 19:56.970
So there's no mistakes.

20:01.845 --> 20:04.220
Was he familiar to you?

20:04.220 --> 20:06.095
-What the hell you mean by that?
-I didn't mean--

20:06.095 --> 20:07.887
What you want me to say?

20:07.887 --> 20:09.595
[woman]
Kayla, he's about to ask--

20:09.595 --> 20:11.720
[Kayla] And I told him already.
He don't believe me.

20:11.720 --> 20:12.970
He thinks I'm lying.

20:14.720 --> 20:15.970
[police radio chatter]

20:17.720 --> 20:19.261
[Decourcy]
Miss Wiley,

20:19.261 --> 20:21.762
I work for the district
attorney's office.

20:21.762 --> 20:24.136
I know it's hard.

20:24.136 --> 20:25.762
It's a hard thing
to think about.

20:25.762 --> 20:28.720
But Siobhan had to answer
the same questions.

20:28.720 --> 20:30.345
So did I.

20:30.345 --> 20:32.428
And the reverend said,

20:32.428 --> 20:34.512
"Look to each other."

20:34.512 --> 20:35.679
Hmm?

20:35.679 --> 20:37.553
I couldn't see
their faces.

20:37.553 --> 20:39.428
Did you know the deceased?

20:41.136 --> 20:42.804
I think I've seen him
before.

20:42.804 --> 20:44.762
Okay.

20:44.762 --> 20:46.595
Let's start there.

20:53.929 --> 20:55.970
Hey. That's your mom?

20:55.970 --> 20:57.887
I didn't even
think of that.

20:59.428 --> 21:00.762
Then who are you
talking to?

21:00.762 --> 21:02.970
Waiting to speak
to our congressman.

21:02.970 --> 21:05.512
-Siobhan.
-He has to hear us now.

21:05.512 --> 21:07.303
-He has to do something.
-Siobhan, listen to me.

21:07.303 --> 21:09.762
-Listen to me.
-What? What do you want from me?

21:09.762 --> 21:10.970
Just... just...

21:10.970 --> 21:12.679
-hey, just give it--
-I have to do--

21:12.679 --> 21:14.470
--a minute.

21:14.470 --> 21:16.470
I have to do something.

21:18.053 --> 21:20.011
Uh--

21:20.011 --> 21:21.804
You should trust me.

21:21.804 --> 21:24.845
Just breathe, baby.

21:24.845 --> 21:26.762
Just breathe.

21:26.762 --> 21:28.804
[sighs]

21:28.804 --> 21:31.762
How is it so easy for you?

21:33.011 --> 21:34.470
It's not my first time.

21:35.553 --> 21:37.845
Oh, man, but...

21:37.845 --> 21:39.053
like that?

21:39.970 --> 21:42.136
You know where I grew up.

21:47.720 --> 21:48.845
It's okay.

21:50.804 --> 21:51.804
It's okay.

21:52.887 --> 21:54.178
All right?

21:55.845 --> 21:57.095
[police radio chatter]

22:02.095 --> 22:04.679
-[siren wailing]
-[Decourcy sighs]

22:16.345 --> 22:18.095
[siren wails]

22:25.011 --> 22:27.762
Counsel, are you
all right?

22:27.762 --> 22:29.512
Where the hell
did you come from?

22:29.512 --> 22:31.136
How's your wife?

22:31.136 --> 22:32.887
Her mom came and got her.

22:32.887 --> 22:35.720
Good, then I can
buy you a drink.

22:35.720 --> 22:38.011
Nah, I got to get
back inside.

22:40.428 --> 22:42.553
Anyone in there
you could talk to?

22:47.929 --> 22:49.387
I...

22:51.095 --> 22:53.553
I-I had my arms up.

22:58.387 --> 23:03.053
Police came, and...
I'm in my own  church.

23:03.053 --> 23:07.512
And I put my arms up
instinctively.

23:07.512 --> 23:09.470
Well, yeah, that was
a smart thing to do.

23:09.470 --> 23:11.595
I'd have done the same thing,
circumstances were the same.

23:11.595 --> 23:14.011
But then again,
I look guilty as fuck.

23:14.011 --> 23:16.804
So that's what's bugging you,
huh? Not something else?

23:16.804 --> 23:19.845
Maybe you're right.
Maybe it is something else.

23:19.845 --> 23:24.470
Maybe I'm upset because
when the shooting was over,

23:24.470 --> 23:26.720
at triage time,

23:26.720 --> 23:29.762
everyone came together--
I didn't.

23:29.762 --> 23:31.303
I went the other way.

23:31.303 --> 23:33.178
[ sighs]
Look, I mean, you know,

23:33.178 --> 23:35.345
you did what you
know how to do.

23:35.345 --> 23:37.011
You don't think that helped?

23:37.011 --> 23:38.887
You don't think you defused
things just a little?

23:38.887 --> 23:41.387
A couple of terrified cops
running into a place

23:41.387 --> 23:43.011
that they know
they're not wanted,

23:43.011 --> 23:44.595
that they don't even belong.

23:44.595 --> 23:46.970
And what do they see?
A prosecutor.

23:46.970 --> 23:49.303
Someone they know
that they can talk to.

23:49.303 --> 23:51.720
No, you're missing the point.

23:51.720 --> 23:54.637
I don't belong
to either side.

23:56.303 --> 23:59.887
Well, one has to pay
at all times,

23:59.887 --> 24:02.887
and sometimes one must pay
rather dearly for being honest.

24:02.887 --> 24:04.595
You know, one of these days

24:04.595 --> 24:06.804
I'm going to end up
reading Lincoln Steffens.

24:06.804 --> 24:08.804
And you're going to have shit
to say to me.

24:08.804 --> 24:11.470
That's someone else, actually.

24:11.470 --> 24:13.720
But my point is this,
and bear with it,

24:13.720 --> 24:16.762
because I am going
to quote someone.

24:16.762 --> 24:20.303
If you go to hunt a lion,
everyone will join.

24:20.303 --> 24:24.637
But you go to hunt a skunk,
and you are alone.

24:24.637 --> 24:27.720
Now you went after
the Boston Police Department.

24:27.720 --> 24:30.720
And then you went
to work with them.

24:30.720 --> 24:32.387
You are alone.

24:32.387 --> 24:35.387
Now maybe you expected
some natural political base,

24:35.387 --> 24:38.178
that neighborhood or the next
one over for doing that,

24:38.178 --> 24:41.679
but maybe you made
some assumptions

24:41.679 --> 24:43.762
based on appearances.

24:43.762 --> 24:47.512
You got to just know that
if you put yourself on the line,

24:47.512 --> 24:50.178
which you are,
opening up this grand jury case,

24:50.178 --> 24:52.345
this job is not
going to be easy.

24:52.345 --> 24:54.095
Your life is going to get
assuredly worse

24:54.095 --> 24:55.887
from here on out.

24:55.887 --> 24:57.011
Trust me.

25:02.845 --> 25:04.637
Hey...

25:06.011 --> 25:07.261
you know why I do
what I do?

25:09.011 --> 25:11.011
I was a kid, right?

25:11.011 --> 25:15.679
I saw Bobby Kennedy
giving shit to Jimmy Hoffa

25:15.679 --> 25:19.178
on a wall of TVs at the window
at Lechmere's.

25:21.387 --> 25:22.970
You know, I'd forgotten
about this.

25:22.970 --> 25:26.095
And then somebody
reminded me about it.

25:26.095 --> 25:29.887
Now, I didn't know
who Bobby Kennedy was.

25:29.887 --> 25:31.720
I didn't know
who his brother was.

25:31.720 --> 25:35.970
But here was this kid
giving shit to adults.

25:35.970 --> 25:37.929
And I wanted to be that.

25:37.929 --> 25:39.553
And when his brother
got elected,

25:39.553 --> 25:41.553
and he was put in charge
of the Justice Department,

25:41.553 --> 25:46.136
becoming a Kennedy G-man
was how my ambition solidified.

25:47.720 --> 25:49.345
Well, look at me now.

25:49.345 --> 25:52.637
I mean, do I look like
one of those New Frontier types,

25:52.637 --> 25:54.720
horn-rimmed glasses
and a Harvard degree?

25:54.720 --> 25:58.345
No.
But I know what I am.

25:58.345 --> 26:00.595
And I know what I do well.

26:00.595 --> 26:04.762
And I know that I couldn't do
what you do.

26:06.387 --> 26:09.011
Guys like me,
we need guys like you.

26:10.595 --> 26:12.595
Are you trying to say
I'm your Jack Kennedy?

26:14.095 --> 26:16.136
Or maybe what your pops was
to Martin Luther King.

26:16.136 --> 26:17.887
[laughs]

26:17.887 --> 26:19.762
What? What?
What's funny?

26:21.762 --> 26:23.929
My father didn't know King.

26:25.220 --> 26:26.720
Hmm.

26:26.720 --> 26:28.428
What about the eye?

26:28.428 --> 26:30.595
It's obviously
genuinely not there.

26:32.303 --> 26:33.845
Your father didn't beat it
out of you?

26:33.845 --> 26:35.011
No.

26:35.011 --> 26:37.136
Cancer, like Peter Falk.

26:37.136 --> 26:38.553
So, what is this?

26:38.553 --> 26:40.303
Some new tactic?

26:40.303 --> 26:42.261
Make me feel bad for the poor
black boy with cancer?

26:42.261 --> 26:44.345
It may be.

26:44.345 --> 26:46.637
[both laughing]

26:48.095 --> 26:49.470
Well...

26:49.470 --> 26:51.970
the bad do understand.

26:53.345 --> 26:55.220
The bad understand.

26:56.637 --> 26:57.637
[glasses clink]

27:00.053 --> 27:02.804
[TV chatter]

27:02.804 --> 27:04.887
[scoffs]
You stupid fuck.

27:04.887 --> 27:07.387
You're lucky I didn't just blow
your fucking head off.

27:07.387 --> 27:09.637
Your ex would have
nowhere to sit.

27:09.637 --> 27:11.970
Oh, what's the matter?
You feeling good tonight?

27:11.970 --> 27:13.512
Don't mention my mother.

27:13.512 --> 27:15.095
No, she's got the Alzheimer's,
right?

27:15.095 --> 27:17.011
-Yeah.
-Oh, yeah, that's too bad.

27:17.011 --> 27:18.845
I bet she wishes she could
remember the night I gave her.

27:18.845 --> 27:21.220
What's the most you ever lost
on a bet, Vito?

27:21.220 --> 27:23.095
Uh, maybe...

27:23.095 --> 27:25.053
150,000.

27:25.053 --> 27:26.345
-On what?
-Miracle on Ice.

27:26.345 --> 27:29.553
Oh. You bet against America?

27:29.553 --> 27:31.345
I don't live in America.
I live in Boston.

27:31.345 --> 27:33.512
Wasn't that Superfight, huh?

27:33.512 --> 27:35.011
Hagler? I look like a sap?

27:35.011 --> 27:36.595
I made a killing
on Hagler-Leonard. Why?

27:36.595 --> 27:38.345
I don't know.
You know, I...

27:38.345 --> 27:41.178
I was just wondering how much
my Super Bowl bet cost you.

27:41.178 --> 27:42.470
[cork pops]

27:42.470 --> 27:43.970
What?

27:43.970 --> 27:45.220
Are you gonna play dumb
with me now?

27:45.220 --> 27:47.220
Oh, Jackie...

27:47.220 --> 27:49.512
You don't remember me sitting
here beginning of last season,

27:49.512 --> 27:51.178
and we were talking
about the time

27:51.178 --> 27:53.470
that all the Indians stole
the Mayflower down in Plymouth.

27:53.470 --> 27:55.095
And I said to you,
"Fuck them,

27:55.095 --> 27:57.553
I'm going to take the Redskins
to win the Super Bowl"?

27:57.553 --> 27:59.929
Why don't you just ask me
for a loan?

27:59.929 --> 28:02.470
Save the effort of coming up
with all of this bullshit.

28:02.470 --> 28:04.428
Because I'm not
paying you back.

28:04.428 --> 28:06.470
You shit bag.

28:06.470 --> 28:08.845
What were the odds?

28:08.845 --> 28:11.970
I think I put down five grand
at five to one.

28:11.970 --> 28:13.845
Fuck you.

28:13.845 --> 28:16.428
-Make it four to one then.
-Not bad enough.

28:16.428 --> 28:18.387
The fucking casinos
in Connecticut are killing me.

28:18.387 --> 28:20.845
I got to deal
with your bullshit too?

28:23.553 --> 28:24.720
[money hits floor]

28:30.053 --> 28:32.053
Hey, Vito...

28:32.053 --> 28:33.637
give your mother my best.

28:33.637 --> 28:35.553
I know I did.

28:35.553 --> 28:37.220
[William Shatner, on TV]
At 11:37 p.m.

28:37.220 --> 28:39.637
911 dispatcher Ken Sirotoski
took the call.

28:39.637 --> 28:41.387
[indistinct radio chatter
over TV]

28:41.387 --> 28:44.095
Take off your shoes.

28:44.095 --> 28:45.720
They're heels, Non.

28:45.720 --> 28:47.720
I just washed
the fucking floor.

28:49.553 --> 28:52.136
Okay, well, you don't have
to wash the floors every day.

28:52.136 --> 28:54.595
What if I fucking
croak tonight?

28:54.595 --> 28:56.303
I ain't gonna have people
coming in here,

28:56.303 --> 28:59.345
despite the rest of you trying,
saying I had a filthy house.

28:59.345 --> 29:01.428
Non, if you croak,

29:01.428 --> 29:02.929
people are going
to come in the house,

29:02.929 --> 29:04.261
get the floors all dirty.

29:04.261 --> 29:05.887
Don't start,
you little bitch.

29:09.220 --> 29:10.929
[telephone rings]

29:13.136 --> 29:14.929
Yeah?

29:14.929 --> 29:17.095
[woman, on phone]
This is O'Rourke residence?

29:17.095 --> 29:18.929
-No, wrong number.
-Oh, I'm sorry.

29:18.929 --> 29:21.637
The Rohr residence?

29:21.637 --> 29:23.720
We tried the office,
but no answer,

29:23.720 --> 29:26.220
and we know he wanted to get
these test results right away.

29:26.220 --> 29:28.011
-Well, who is this?
-The free clinic.

29:28.011 --> 29:30.136
We have John Rohr's
blood tests back.

29:30.136 --> 29:32.637
He is disease-free.

29:32.637 --> 29:34.637
-Disease-free?
-Blood was clean.

29:34.637 --> 29:37.720
No sign of sexually transmitted
disease.

29:37.720 --> 29:39.428
[door opens]

29:41.720 --> 29:43.220
[door closes]

29:43.220 --> 29:45.053
[keys rattle]

29:50.345 --> 29:52.637
Ah! Aren't they supposed
to play theme music

29:52.637 --> 29:54.512
when you're about
to appear?

29:54.512 --> 29:56.178
Cloud of flying monkeys
or something?

29:56.178 --> 29:58.095
Keep fucking laughing, idiot.

29:58.095 --> 30:02.053
You'll need a sense of humor
in your new lonely life.

30:02.053 --> 30:03.553
You pig.

30:03.553 --> 30:05.470
You don't think
anyone knows.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.970
But you didn't think
to wrap it up.

30:07.970 --> 30:09.679
What the fuck
are you talking about?

30:09.679 --> 30:11.428
Doctor called.

30:11.428 --> 30:13.303
The free clinic.

30:13.303 --> 30:15.178
So what?

30:15.178 --> 30:17.345
I went for an EKG.

30:17.345 --> 30:18.345
Bullshit.

30:18.345 --> 30:20.512
You got cooties.

30:20.512 --> 30:23.637
What did they say?

30:23.637 --> 30:26.303
You're infected,
you piece of shit.

30:29.470 --> 30:31.178
I've been telling
my daughter for years

30:31.178 --> 30:33.345
that you've got a wandering
eyeball, but she was always--

30:33.345 --> 30:36.679
You don't tell Jenny nothing.
You fucking hear me?

30:36.679 --> 30:39.053
You think I'm going to let you
infect my kid?

30:39.053 --> 30:40.887
You out of your mind?

30:40.887 --> 30:42.470
How do you know
that she don't got it?

30:42.470 --> 30:45.261
How do you know that she didn't
give it to me?

30:45.261 --> 30:48.011
You think I don't know
what goes on in my own house?

31:00.553 --> 31:01.887
Joe made this, right?

31:04.136 --> 31:05.553
Put that back.

31:05.553 --> 31:08.595
This is the Red Baron plane,
isn't it?

31:08.595 --> 31:10.887
Yeah, it seems--
it seems very intricate.

31:13.053 --> 31:15.637
You've been treating me
like trash since day one.

31:15.637 --> 31:17.261
You and him both.

31:17.261 --> 31:18.595
And you want
to bust your daughter

31:18.595 --> 31:19.762
all the time
for being clueless,

31:19.762 --> 31:21.512
but you got shit
that you're never going

31:21.512 --> 31:22.887
to want to admit to yourself.

31:22.887 --> 31:26.053
You put me
in the fucking doghouse,

31:26.053 --> 31:28.136
and I'm going to be like Snoopy
and blow your shit

31:28.136 --> 31:29.595
right the fuck
out of the sky.

31:29.595 --> 31:31.387
You know me, you bitch.

31:31.387 --> 31:33.804
You think I'm going to start
fighting fair with you?

31:33.804 --> 31:35.637
So, what are you
going to do?

31:35.637 --> 31:38.053
-You really want to test me?
-No, no, no, don't!

31:40.387 --> 31:42.220
Come on.

31:42.220 --> 31:47.136
Now, you really think
that I'm that inhuman?

31:47.136 --> 31:50.929
I mean, give me some credit,
for Christ's sake.

32:04.053 --> 32:05.595
[door slamming]

32:05.595 --> 32:08.345
[mellow jazz plays
over car radio]

32:08.345 --> 32:09.345
[door slamming]

32:14.345 --> 32:15.470
[knocks]

32:18.804 --> 32:21.136
You ever going
to come out of there?

32:23.303 --> 32:25.553
The church.

32:25.553 --> 32:28.095
I don't want to hear everybody's
questions and concerns.

32:28.095 --> 32:30.804
It's a good thing
no one likes you then, huh?

32:32.804 --> 32:34.553
How's our friend
in Fall River?

32:34.553 --> 32:35.887
Like you said,

32:35.887 --> 32:37.762
Watergate kid was a setup.

32:37.762 --> 32:38.804
Was Hannihan just a shit cop,

32:38.804 --> 32:40.637
or was he protecting somebody
on this?

32:40.637 --> 32:42.428
It could be both.

32:42.428 --> 32:45.095
This must really dim your faith
in the Boston Police Department.

32:52.428 --> 32:54.512
[Decourcy]
Got to find those bodies.

32:56.762 --> 32:58.470
♪ suspenseful music plays ♪

33:45.762 --> 33:47.303
Witness changed
his statement.

33:47.303 --> 33:48.387
Who?

33:51.053 --> 33:53.887
Thomas Hayes. See, the night
Kinicki disappears,

33:53.887 --> 33:55.637
he tells the first
detective on scene

33:55.637 --> 33:57.011
that he didn't see anything.

33:57.011 --> 33:58.387
He says Kinicki went
to the bathroom

33:58.387 --> 33:59.595
and he never comes back.

33:59.595 --> 34:01.762
But he testifies...

34:01.762 --> 34:04.220
-He testified?
-He testified at trial...

34:05.720 --> 34:08.595
